
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `basename` ghesmate paayaniek path file ra joda mikonad. Be ebarate digar, name asli file ya directory ra bedune path-e kamel ya pasvand (extension) namayesh midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `basename PATH` --> 📁 Name file ya directory ra az PATH joda mikonad.
    🔹 `basename PATH SUFFIX` --> ✂️ Agar PATH ba SUFFIX tamoom shavad, suffix ra hazf mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ basename /home/user/documents/myfile.txt

    🔹 Namayesh: myfile.txt

    $ basename /home/user/documents/myfile.txt .txt

    🔹 Namayesh: myfile

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ basename /var/log/apache2/error.log

    🔹 Agar name file "error.log" bashad va path an "/var/log/apache2/" bashad, dastoor "error.log" ra chap mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `basename` command isolates the last component of a file path. In other words, it displays the actual name of the file or directory, removing the complete path or a specified suffix (extension).

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `basename PATH` --> 📁 Extracts the file or directory name from PATH.
    🔹 `basename PATH SUFFIX` --> ✂️ If PATH ends with SUFFIX, it removes the suffix.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ basename /home/user/documents/myfile.txt

    🔹 Output: myfile.txt

    $ basename /home/user/documents/myfile.txt .txt

    🔹 Output: myfile

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ basename /var/log/apache2/error.log

    🔹 If the file is named "error.log" and located in "/var/log/apache2/", the command will print "error.log".

